{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Pastry","content":["Preheat oven to 180°C and set aside 12 mini loose-bottom tartlet tins (3.5 cm base).","Place egg and sugar into mixing bowl and mix <nobr>20 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>.","Add butter, lime zest and flour and mix <nobr>20 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Transfer pastry onto a silicone bread mat or lightly floured work surface and shape into a ball. Wrap in plastic wrap and place into refrigerator to chill (approx. 30 minutes).","Roll out pastry to approx. 5 mm thick. Using a round cookie cutter (10 cm), cut out 12 pastry rounds and press into mini tartlet tins. Dock each pastry case with a fork, line with baking paper and fill with pie weights, rice or dried beans.  Bake for 12 minutes (180°C) or until dry to the touch. Set aside to cool completely, then remove from tins. Clean and dry mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Lime curd","content":[" <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place all Lime curd ingredients into mixing bowl and cook <nobr>20 min\/80°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Spoon 2 teaspoons of curd into base of each pastry case, then place onto a baking tray (30 x 40 cm). Thoroughly clean and dry mixing bowl and butterfly whisk."]},{"title":"Meringue","content":["Increase oven to 200°C. <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place egg whites and cream of tartar into mixing bowl and whip <nobr>2 min\/70°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>, <strong>without measuring cup<\/strong>, until stiff peaks form.","Add vanilla paste and cook <nobr>2 min\/60°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>, adding icing sugar 1 tablespoon at a time through hole in mixing bowl lid. Cook for a further <nobr>5 min\/60°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>.","Transfer meringue into a piping bag fitted with a plain nozzle (1 cm) and decorate the top of each tart as desired. Bake for 10 minutes (200°C) or until meringue is lightly browned. Remove from oven and transfer onto a wire rack to cool completely (approx. 1 hour) before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Pastry","content":["1 egg","50 g caster sugar","120 g unsalted butter, cut into pieces","1 lime, zest only (no white pith)","220 g plain flour"]},{"title":"Lime curd","content":["120 g caster sugar","3 fresh limes, juice only (approx. 60 g)","1 tsp cornflour","60 g unsalted butter, cut into pieces","3 egg yolks"]},{"title":"Meringue","content":["2 egg whites, room temperature","¼ tsp cream of tartar","½ tsp vanilla bean paste","100 g icing sugar (see Tips)"]}],"id":"r281389","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-R9aUo8msq40\/XZWqNLVwrNI\/AAAAAAAAfUg\/KBMfOuGGEWsFeJOMf4LRyNH01n3iWlTjgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_FReFHZqPJ55aWWtl.png","title":"Lime meringue tartlets","publishedAt":"2018-05-10T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4.1 g","fat":"14 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"36.2 g","calories":"1198.9 kJ \/ 285.4 kcal"},"usefulItems":"silicone bread mat, rolling pin, pie weights, rice or dried beans, round cookie cutter (10 cm), piping bag with a plain nozzle (1 cm), mini loose-bottom tartlet tins (3.5 cm), plastic wrap, baking paper, baking tray (30 x 40 cm), wire rack, fork, oven, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["To make your own icing sugar, please refer to the recipe in <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> or <i>Everyday Cookbook<\/i>.","To save time, make the lime curd while pastry cases are baking and cooling."],"basicInfo":["easy","35m","2h 40m","12 portions"]}